03-Models for 2yr dataset

Francisco E. Fonturbel

16/ago/2023

Anthropogenic effects on chungungos abundance

Here we will explore some anthropogenic variables as potential drivers of abundance change on this species

Lets do some nice ggplots to examine our data before fitting fancy models:

How is our response varible distributed?

Well, our response variable is not normal, as abundance is a count variable with positive integers. Therefore, we should use Poisson or negative binomial distributions instead.

Individual models

Although is not the best option, we will try to fit some glms for each individual predictor variable depicted in the plots above.

Lets test our count variable for overdispersion before continuing

## 
##  Overdispersion test
## 
## data:  modp
## z = -0.57178, p-value = 0.7163
## alternative hypothesis: true dispersion is greater than 1
## sample estimates:
## dispersion 
##  0.9368539

No overdispersion, we can go with Poisson distribution hereafter.
